Class BoundingBox

  • java.lang.Object
    • database.BoundingBox

      • findAttractionsBetween

        public static List<AttractionNode> findAttractionsBetween​(double[] coords1,
                                                          double[] coords2,
                                                          List<String> categories,
                                                          int prefNumStops,
                                                          int costPref,
                                                          double[] preferredStop)
        Creates a bounding box around the given starting and end positions, and returns a list of the AttractionNodes from the yelp-database within this box that are of the given categories.
        Parameters:
        coords1 - - [lat, lon] of the start position
        coords2 - - [lat, lon] of the end position
        categories - - list of acceptable attraction categories
        prefNumStops - - number of stops user prefers to make
        costPref - - cost preference of user
        preferredStop - - list of doubles representing users preference for each stop type
        Returns:
        list of attraction nodes of the given categories within a box around the given positions

      • findAttractionsWithinBoundingBox

        public static List<AttractionNode> findAttractionsWithinBoundingBox​(double[] boundingBoxBounds,
                                                                    List<String> categories,
                                                                    int prefNumStops,
                                                                    int costPref,
                                                                    double[] preferredStop)
                                                             throws SQLException,
                                                                    IOException
        Returns a list of all the attractions in the yelp database within the given bounding box that are of the given categories.
        Parameters:
        boundingBoxBounds - - [start lat, end lat, start lon, end lon] of the bounding box
        categories - - list of acceptable attraction categories
        prefNumStops - - number of stops preferred by user
        costPref - - cost preference of user
        preferredStop - - double representing user's value preference of each stop type
        Returns:
        list of attraction nodes of the given categories within the given bounding box
        Throws:
        SQLException - - if yelp database cannot be successfully queried
        IOException - - if issue with yelp API connection
